1 olive oil
1 Wholemeal Panini
1 packet chicken breast
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
2 cucumber
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 bag slaw mix

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut or tear wholemeal panini into bite-sized chunks.
• Place panini on a lined oven tray, drizzle with olive oil and season with salt
and pepper.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until golden, 5-7 minutes. Set aside to cool slightly.

Little cooks: Help tear the panini!

• While the croutons are cooking, combine chicken breast and Aussie spice blend in a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat and cook chicken until browned, 2-3 minutes each side.
• Transfer chicken to a second lined oven tray and bake until cooked through, 10-12 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice cucumber.
• In a large bowl, combine dill & parsley mayonnaise, a drizzle of olive oil and a splash of water.
• Add slaw mix, cucumber and croutons. Season and toss to combine.

Little cooks: Take the lead by combining the ingredients for the slaw!

• Slice golden chicken.
• Divide crouton slaw with herby-mayo dressing between plates.
• Top with chicken, spooning over any resting juices. Enjoy!